description:
&lt;p&gt;Priory Hospital Church Village is situated in Tonteg near Pontypridd in South Wales. The Hospital provides assessment and treatment for women between the ages of 18 and 65 with a mild to moderate learning disability, who may also have a borderline personality disorder and associated mental health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To assist and support staff in the management of the ward and to ensure that in their absence, the effective management of the ward is maintained. As a Bank Staff Nurse you will be working within a team that includes a range of professionals. You will be central to providing high quality care within a Hospital that provides assessment and treatment for women between the ages of 18 and 65 with a mild to moderate learning disability, who may also have a borderline personality disorder and associated mental health problems..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Skills/Knowledge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication skills&lt;br /&gt;Ability to work flexibility&lt;br /&gt;Basic Literacy skills&lt;br /&gt;Basic Knowledge of general mental health issues&lt;br /&gt;Common sense approach to problem solving.&lt;br /&gt;Basic numeracy skills&lt;br /&gt;Some appreciation of Mental Health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RMN / RNLD /RMNH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pre-registration – complete / Preceptorship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
